claim.claim-text:
21. A method for use in fabricating semiconductor devices, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing a first region of material; 
forming a second region of material at a position relative to the first region of material, the second region of material having a surface in contact with and extending from the first region of material; 
forming a disposable spacer from a germanium-silicon alloy on a portion of the surface of the second region of material, the disposable spacer extending over a first portion of the first region of material; and 
implanting a second portion of the first region of material offset relative to the second region of material by the disposable spacer.

28. A method for use in fabricating semiconductor devices, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing a first region of material; 
forming a second region of material at a position relative to the first region of material; 
forming a disposable spacer of germanium-silicon alloy in contact with a portion of the second region of material; and 
etching the first region of material offset relative to the second region of material by the disposable spacer.

30. A method for use in the fabrication of MOS devices, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing a substrate having a gate structure formed thereon, the gate structure including at least one sidewall; 
forming a germanium-silicon layer over the gate structure and substrate; 
forming a disposable spacer from the germanium-silicon layer on the at least one sidewall; and 
implanting a portion of the substrate offset from the gate structure by the disposable spacer.

36. A method for use in the fabrication of semiconductor devices, the method comprising the steps of: 
providing a substrate having an oxidation mask thereon, the oxidation mask including at least one sidewall; 
forming oxide on the substrate; 
forming a germanium-silicon layer over the oxidation mask and substrate; 
forming a disposable spacer using the germanium-silicon layer on the at least one sidewall; and 
implanting a portion of the substrate offset from the oxidation mask by the disposable spacer.

43. A method for use in the fabrication of semiconductor devices, the method comprising: 
providing a substrate having an oxidation mask thereon, wherein the oxidation mask comprises at least one sidewall; 
forming oxide on the substrate; 
forming a germanium-silicon layer over the oxidation mask and substrate; 
forming a disposable spacer using the germanium-silicon layer on the at least one sidewall; and 
implanting a portion of the substrate offset from the oxidation mask by the disposable spacer.

52. A method for use in the fabrication of semiconductor devices, the method comprising: 
providing a substrate having an oxidation mask thereon, wherein the oxidation mask comprises at least one sidewall; 
forming oxide on the substrate; 
forming a germanium-silicon layer over the oxidation mask and substrate; 
forming a disposable spacer using the germanium-silicon layer on the at least one sidewall; 
implanting a portion of the substrate offset from the oxidation mask by the disposable spacer; and 
etching a trench in the substrate offset from the oxidation mask by the disposable spacer.

61. A method for use in the fabrication of semiconductor devices, the method comprising: 
providing a substrate having an oxidation mask thereon, wherein the oxidation mask comprises at least one sidewall; 
forming oxide on the substrate; 
forming a germanium-silicon layer over the oxidation mask and substrate; 
forming a disposable spacer using the germanium-silicon layer on the at least one sidewall, wherein the disposable spacer comprises a first portion (x) of germanium and a second portion (1-x) of silicon, wherein x is greater than about 0.7; and 
implanting a portion of the substrate offset from the oxidation mask by the disposable spacer.

68. A method for use in fabricating semiconductor devices, the method comprising: 
providing a first region of material and a second region of material positioned relative to the first region of material; 
forming a disposable spacer using a germanium-silicon alloy adjacent a portion of both the first region of material and second region of material; 
materially altering a portion of the first region of material offset relative to the second region of material by the disposable spacer, wherein materially altering a portion of the first region of material comprises: 
ion implanting the portion of the first region of material offset relative to the second region of material by the disposable spacer; and 
etching the portion of the first region of material offset relative to the second region of material by the disposable spacer.
